DoubleStar Corp’s Origin
Many people ask “where did DSC come from?” After 25 years of success with J&T Distributing selling black rifle parts and accessories, Teresa and Jesse Starnes(Double-Starnes’) decided to create a full line of complete weapons to satisfy the thousands of requests to build an AR-15. Differences in AR-15 type rifles?

USGI and/or mil-spec.: 
Commercial parts are made by casting and stamping, which requires weaker, softer steel to do. Parts wear out faster. USGI and mil-spec are forged and milled, much harder steel. And commercial parts don’t always work with mil-spec if you need a replacement, whereas all mil-spec works with all mil-spec. 

The DoubleStar costs more, but it is all USGI, all mil-spec. The DS-4 is a rifle with flattop. It does not come with a rear sight. They do that due to differences in personal preference. 
The DS-4 Comes with magazine and manual.

The DoubleStar is USGI, M16 blueprint (no others can say that), all parts x-rayed and particle tested. Carrier is internally lined for the bolt travel and typically has a chrome firing pin. 

Finish and machining on the DS is far superior to most all manufacturers, and they use a higher grade 7075 aluminum. Most commercial manufacturers use 6061 aluminum, substandard and not mil-spec. 

I can go on and on. Only the billet and really high dollar manufacturers can really even compare to DoubleStar… And if I was to stake my life on it, I would want it to be the DoubleStar…

postcontent:
NEW Adams Arms AR-15 A3 Base Mid Length Gas Piston Upper Assembly. Piston AR15s are a big improvement in reliability over the direct impingement AR. $930 plus $24.99 Priority shipping. I paid nearly $1000 for this after shipping and tax, so I'm not looking to make much profit.

Specifications:

-Barrel Finish: QPQ Melonite / Black Nitride
-Twist Rate: 1 in 7"

-M4 Feed Ramps: Yes
-Bolt Carrier: 1-Piece w/Integral Piston Strike Face
-Muzzle Device: A2 Flash Hider
-Gas Block Diameter: 0.750"
-Extras: One 4" Rail Section, QD Sling Swivel Mount, Single Rail Piston Gas Block
-Weight: 4.64 lbs (Without Rail Sections)

$999 plus $24.99 Priority Mail shipping with Signature Confirmation. Insurance is $20 extra.

 I accept money order and discrete PayPal (3% extra for regular, no fee with Gift). Item ships in 2-3 business days. Feel free to call me at REDACTED if you have any questions.

===============
===============
This Adams Arms AR-15 A3 Base MOE Mid Length Gas Piston Upper Assembly is chambered in 5.56x45mm NATO and comes ready to fire right out of the box upon installation onto any standard AR-15 lower receiver. This Base Mid upper comes equipped with a 16" melonite-finished barrel, A2 flash hider, bolt carrier group, charging handle, picatinny rail gas block, delta ring assembly and a set of black Magpul MOE polymer handguards. Additional features include a forged A3 flat-top configuration that's ready to accept the shooter's choice of optic and/or rear iron sight, M4 feed ramps to help ensure reliable feeding and functioning during rapid strings of fire, and a mid length gas system for a smoother recoil impulse and longer sight radius. 

The upper's barrel has been finished inside and out with Adams Arms' proprietary QPQ Melonite treatment that bonds with the metal on a molecular level. Also referred to as salt bath nitriding, this treatment produces an extremely hard, slick surface on steel that resists carbon adhesion and increases corrosion resistance, extending a barrel's service life by reducing the friction produced inside the bore upon firing for a net decrease in bore surface wear over time. Nitriding converts the barrel steel's surface without any build-up, retaining all of the benefits of traditional chrome lining without suffering the accuracy degradation commonly encountered with it due to the uneven application of chrome inside the barrel's bore. The end result is a barrel that's capable of producing accuracy on par with a match stainless steel tube, while also exhibiting the longevity and resilience of a chrome lined, mil-spec barrel. 

All Adams Arms uppers feature a short stroke gas piston operating system, which prevents hot gas and debris from being directed back into the action upon firing. The result is a rifle that runs cooler, cleaner and more reliably than those utilizing a standard direct gas impingement system of operation. To ensure that damage doesn't occur to the buffer tube from carrier tilt, the bolt carrier is equipped with enlarged "skis" to help guide it into the receiver extension. The bolt carrier's solid steel, 1-piece construction incorporates an integral piston strike face to guarantee integrity over time, while the bolt assembly is spring loaded for proper lock-up and to help reduce bolt bounce and cam pin wear. All piston components are finished in QPQ Melonite for corrosion resistance and easy cleaning/maintenance.

title: For Sale/Trade:  "Classic" 1964 RED Thunderbird with the Limited 390 cid Engine
postcontent:
Classic 1964 RED Thunderbird with the Limited 390 cid Engine

Asking $4,000 or Trade for Quality Firearms + Cash

NADA-Values
Low Retail 2013 $8808.00 
Average Retail 2013 $14,985 
High Retail 2013 $21,600
The V8 Engine +A/C adds additional 35% value 

This is a Rare 1964 Thunderbird. This one has every option that was available at the time.
Air Conditioning 
Cruise Control 
Power steering & Power Brakes 
Remote trunk release 
Power seats & Power windows 
Original Radio AM (FM wasn't available yet)
Low fuel light. 
There is even a rear vent just below the rear window to pull the cigarette smoke from the interior.
This is the only Year that Ford spelled "Thunderbird" in individual letters across the front of the Hood.

1964 Thunderbird with the Limited 390 cid engine. The overall condition is pretty good. There are a couple of small dents on each lower front fender (car dolly damage during transport). There is a small spot of rust on the driver side quarter panel near the door. Overall the body is remarkably straight! 
The car was being restored in 2002 until the original owner suffered a stroke and it sat in a Garage for the next Seven (7) years. The car was sold to a coworker who in turn sold it to a Deputy Sherriff in Lake George (This is where I step in). The Engine Compartment was detailed at that time with new AC Lines, Power Steering Lines, Vacuum Lines and Cans, Plug Wires, Power Steering Pump, Hoses, Battery, and lots more. . . The Front Brakes are new (Drums, Shoes, and Cylinders). The Front Wheel Bearings are also new.
When I purchased it, most of the Major Work on the Engine had been completed but it had not been driven much (if at all). I loaded it on a Flat-Bed for the trip from Lake George to Colorado Springs. 
The Interior is Black Leather and in pretty Great Condition for being Original. The motors and regulators on the Windows have been removed to be repaired and are in the trunk.
The Steering Gear Box and the Brake Booster have been rebuilt in Denver Recently. The Steering Flex Coupler has been replaced as Well.
The paint is fair except for a plate sized spot where the paint on the hood was removed. It appears to have been exposed to break fluid during the Brake Rebuild. 
The Car is Essentially Complete with No Missing Chrome or Other Parts. (Pretty Unbelievable in itself)
The Front Tires are BRAND NEW and the Rear Tires are Near New. 

WHAT NEEDS TO BE DONE. . . 
Finally, the Gas in the Tank was Old and had fouled the Gas Tank and the Fuel Sending and Float Unit. I have Purchased New OEM Period Factory Parts (Tank, Sending Unit with Float and Reserve Fuel Light Indicator. These are mounted in the New Gas Tank but the Tank has NOT yet been installed.
